2014 HMIS API documentation version 1.1.0

https://www.hmislynk.com/hmis-clientapi/rest/v2014

/clients

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS clients within the system, and for adding a new client to the set of clients

/clients get post

get

Searches for client. Returns a list of client ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a client

get /clients

Searches for client. Returns a list of client ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0

The HMIS API supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

HTTP status code 404

Not found â€“ There is no resource behind the URI.

Internal Server Error

Secured by oauth_2_0

Headers

  • Authorization: required (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use an "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or the HMIS revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/clients/{clientid} get put delete

Operations performed on a single HMIS client within the system.

get

Gets a client using a URI resource parameter/ID.

put

Updates a specific client specified by the URI resource parameter/ID.

delete

Deletes a specific client specified by the URI resource parameter/ID.

get /clients/{clientid}

Gets a client using a URI resource parameter/ID.

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS enrollments within the system, and for adding a new enrollment to the set of enrollments

get

Searches for enrollment. Returns a list of enrollment ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a enrollment

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments

Searches for enrollment. Returns a list of enrollment ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0

The HMIS API supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests.

  • Response

  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    10-11-2012

Unauthorized â€“ The request requires user authentication.

Headers

  • Authorization: required (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use an "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 403

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/commercialsexualexploitations get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS commercialsexualexploitations within the system, and for adding a new commercialsexualexploitation to the set of commercialsexualexploitations

get

Searches for commercialsexualexploitation. Returns a list of commercialsexualexploitation ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a commercialsexualexploitation

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/commercialsexualexploitations

Searches for commercialsexualexploitation. Returns a list of commercialsexualexploitation ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • clientid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V
  • enrollmentid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/dateofengagements get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS dateofengagements within the system, and for adding a new dateofengagement to the set of dateofengagements

get

Searches for dateofengagement. Returns a list of dateofengagement ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a dateofengagement

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/dateofengagements

Searches for dateofengagement. Returns a list of dateofengagement ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    Example:

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/domesticviolences get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS domesticviolences within the system, and for adding a new domesticviolence to the set of domesticviolences

get

Searches for domesticviolence. Returns a list of domesticviolence ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a domesticviolence

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/domesticviolences

Searches for domesticviolence. Returns a list of domesticviolence ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

get

post

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/exits

Searches for exit. Returns a list of exit ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0

The HMIS API supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • clientid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V
  • enrollmentid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

                      "pagination": {
                        "id": "pagination",
                        "type": "object",
                        "properties": {
                          "from": {
                            "id": "from",
                            "type": "integer"
                          },
                          "returned": {
                            "id": "returned",
                            "type": "integer"
                          },
                          "total": {
                            "id": "total",
                            "type": "integer"
                          },
                          "maximum": {
                            "id": "maximum",
                            "type": "integer"
                          },
                          "sort": {
                            "id": "sort",
                            "type": "object",
                            "properties": {}
                          }
                        },
                        "required": [
                          "from",
                          "returned",
                          "total",
                          "maximum",
                          "sort"
                        ]
                      },
                      "exits": {
                        "id": "exits",
                        "type": "array",
                        "items": {

  • exitid: required (string)

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/healthstatuses get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS healthstatuses within the system, and for adding a new healthstatus to the set of healthstatuses

get

Searches for healthstatus. Returns a list of healthstatus ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a healthstatus

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/healthstatuses

Searches for healthstatus. Returns a list of healthstatus ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0

The HMIS API supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • clientid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V
  • enrollmentid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/incomeandsources get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS incomeandsources within the system, and for adding a new incomeandsource to the set of incomeandsources

get

Searches for incomeandsource. Returns a list of incomeandsource ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a incomeandsource

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/incomeandsources

Searches for incomeandsource. Returns a list of incomeandsource ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/lastgradecompleteds

Searches for lastgradecompleted. Returns a list of lastgradecompleted ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0

The HMIS API supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • clientid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V
  • enrollmentid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/noncashbenefits get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS noncashbenefits within the system, and for adding a new noncashbenefit to the set of noncashbenefits

get

Searches for noncashbenefit. Returns a list of noncashbenefit ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a noncashbenefit

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/noncashbenefits

Searches for noncashbenefit. Returns a list of noncashbenefit ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V
  • enrollmentid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

get

post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS rhybcpstatuses within the system, and for adding a new rhybcpstatus to the set of rhybcpstatuses

  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/schoolstatuses

Searches for schoolstatus. Returns a list of schoolstatus ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

  • Response

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/sexualorientations get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS sexualorientations within the system, and for adding a new sexualorientation to the set of sexualorientations

get

post

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/sexualorientations

Searches for sexualorientation. Returns a list of sexualorientation ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

HTTP status code 400

Bad Request â€“ The request was invalid or cannot be served.

HTTP status code 403

Forbidden â€“ The server understood the request, but is refusing it or the access is not allowed.

HTTP status code 404

Not found â€“ There is no resource behind the URI.

HTTP status code 500

Internal Server Error

Secured by oauth_2_0

Headers

  • Authorization: required (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use an "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or the HMIS revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or the HMIS revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

/clients/{clientid}/veteraninfos get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS veteraninfos within the system, and for adding a new veteraninfo to the set of veteraninfos

get

Searches for veteraninfo. Returns a list of veteraninfo ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a veteraninfo

Searches for veteraninfo. Returns a list of veteraninfo ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    10-11-2012

/projects/{projectid}/inventories get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS inventories within the system, and for adding a new inventory to the set of inventories

get

Searches for inventory. Returns a list of inventory ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a inventory

get /projects/{projectid}/inventories

Searches for inventory. Returns a list of inventory ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

  • Response
  • Security

  • projectid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

Searches for projectcoc. Returns a list of projectcoc ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a projectcoc

get /projects/{projectid}/projectcocs

Searches for projectcoc. Returns a list of projectcoc ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0

The HMIS API supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • projectid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

            "principalsite":0,
            "state":"AK",
            "zip":"1212",
            "dateCreated":"03-15-2016",
            "dateUpdated":"03-15-2016"
         }
}

HTTP status code 200

OK â€“ Everything is working.

HTTP status code 304

Not Modified â€“ The client can use cached data.

HTTP status code 400

Bad Request â€“ The request was invalid or cannot be served.

HTTP status code 401

Unauthorized â€“ The request requires a user.

HTTP status code 403

Forbidden â€“ The server understood the request, but is refusing it or the access is not allowed.

HTTP status code 404

Not found â€“ There is no resource behind the URI.

HTTP status code 500

Internal Server Error.

Secured by oauth_2_0

Headers

  • Authorization: required (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use an "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or the HMIS revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/search

The Search API is optimized to find the specific entity you're looking for (e.g., a client, enrollments, etc.). It's designed to find the one result you're looking for (or maybe the few results you're looking for). Currently hmislynk supporting search on 'clients' entity only. Just like searching on Google, you sometimes want to see a few pages of search results so that you can find the item that best meets your needs. HMISLynk Search API provides up to 50 results for each search. However, the search results can be limited by the client. Note: Current supporting URI is /search/clients .

/search/{searchentity} get

get

get /search/{searchentity}

Secured by oauth_2_0

The HMIS API supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • searchentity: required (string)

Query Parameters

  • q: required (string)

    The search keywords, as well as any qualifiers. Currently supported search fields are first name,middle name,last name,dob,source system id and ssn. For search on "date of birth" field the format MM-dd-YYYY should be used for the search keyword.

  • sort: required (string)

    The sort field. Default- results are sorted by "created date".

    Example:

    created date
  • order: required (string - default: desc)

    The sort order if sort parameter is provided. One of asc or desc. Default- desc.

    Example:

    desc
  • startIndex: required (integer - default: 0)

    The start Index from where the search results should be returned. Default - 0

    Example:

    0
  • maxItems: required (integer - default: 50)

    the number or Items that should be included in the results . Default - 50

    Example:

    50
  • exclude: required (string)

    Excludes fields from the search. Currently its only supported value is "ssi" (to exclude source system id) only.

HTTP status code 200

Body

Media type: application/json

Type: object

Example:

  "pagination": {

    "from": "0",
    "maximum": "50",
